    <!-- Add Activity -->

    <activity>
        <statement>

            <p>
                A square is divided into <m>4</m> equal smaller squares by splitting it into a <m>2 \times 2</m> grid.
            </p>

            <p>
                At each new stage, <em>every square</em> is divided again into <m>4</m> equal smaller squares.
            </p>

            <p>
                <term>Work in groups:</term>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>Draw Stage <m>1</m>, Stage <m>2</m> and Stage <m>3</m> of this process.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Count the total number of small squares at each stage.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Record your results in a table.</p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
                <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                    <row header="yes">
                        <cell>Stage (n)</cell>
                        <cell>Number of squares</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>1</cell>
                        <cell>1</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>2</cell>
                        <cell>4</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>3</cell>
                        <cell>16</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>4</cell>
                        <cell>64</cell>
                    </row>
                </tabular>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(i)">
                    <li>
                        <p>Describe how the number of squares changes from one stage to the next.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>What is the common ratio?</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Write the sequence formed.</p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>

            <p>
                <term>Discussion:</term>
            </p>

            <p>
                The numbers form the sequence:
                <m>1, 4, 16, 64, \dots</m>
            </p>

            <p>
                Each term is obtained by multiplying the previous term by 4.
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(i)">
                    <li>
                        <p>What will be the number of squares at Stage 5? Stage 6?</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Is it practical to keep counting for very large stages?</p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            <p>
                <term>Generalising:</term>
            </p>

            <p>
                Let:
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>First term <m>= a</m></p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Common ratio <m>= r</m></p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            <p>
                <term>Task:</term>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(i)">
                    <li>
                        <p>Write Stage 2 in terms of <m>a</m> and <m>r</m>.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Write Stage 3 in terms of <m>a</m> and <m>r</m>.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Write Stage 4 in terms of <m>a</m> and <m>r</m>.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Identify the pattern and write an expression for Stage <m>n</m>.</p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
    </activity>

